node.text: Hydra, also known as the water snake, is the largest constellation in the sky. It covers 3% of the celestial sphere. In mythology, hydra is depicted as a 9-headed sea monster with one immortal head. If you cut off one hydra head, two more would grow back in its place. In the sky, hydra is only shown with one head - maybe that’s the immortal one? 🐍
